<subSubSection id="162CF771A7E4FC0C467F9E99D1B7A6EA" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="description">
<paragraph id="691A47C4FA68B24C456FFD86F1D18652" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Supplementary description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1825BF1DE7DD997E3FA7992B7F46488" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="8597EA508F512CEBCE88C81339FAD038" bold="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="C2CE2D4D60467562DC7F1D132C032FA2" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Female genitalia</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Tergite IX (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EB4D76D8BBFA7086F29A400DDF329912" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Betacixius maculosus Tsaur &amp; Hsu, 1991, female A genitalia, lateral view B genitalia, ventral view C anal segment, dorsal view D tergite IX, caudal view E gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, ventral view F gonapophysis IX, lateral view G gonoplac, inner lateral view H posterior vagina, ventral view I posterior vagina, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.956.50195.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439750" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">5A, B, D</figureCitation>
) moderately sclerotized, with a medium-sized, nearly dumbbell-shaped wax plate. Anal segment (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8AAA6F7557C9060492D81BEF4F96EAC1" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Betacixius maculosus Tsaur &amp; Hsu, 1991, female A genitalia, lateral view B genitalia, ventral view C anal segment, dorsal view D tergite IX, caudal view E gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, ventral view F gonapophysis IX, lateral view G gonoplac, inner lateral view H posterior vagina, ventral view I posterior vagina, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.956.50195.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439750" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">5C</figureCitation>
) rectangular, slightly widening to apex, 1.1 times longer than wide in dorsal view, anal style finger-like. Gonapophysis VIII (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5195CE01B2BA970450B5002CA44115E0" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Betacixius maculosus Tsaur &amp; Hsu, 1991, female A genitalia, lateral view B genitalia, ventral view C anal segment, dorsal view D tergite IX, caudal view E gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, ventral view F gonapophysis IX, lateral view G gonoplac, inner lateral view H posterior vagina, ventral view I posterior vagina, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.956.50195.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439750" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">5E</figureCitation>
) elongate, and slightly curved upwards. Gonapophysis IX (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B83810B230F17E8FC49AF7E522D071EF" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Betacixius maculosus Tsaur &amp; Hsu, 1991, female A genitalia, lateral view B genitalia, ventral view C anal segment, dorsal view D tergite IX, caudal view E gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, ventral view F gonapophysis IX, lateral view G gonoplac, inner lateral view H posterior vagina, ventral view I posterior vagina, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.956.50195.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439750" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">5F</figureCitation>
) with two middle teeth, distance ratio between distal middle tooth to apex and length of denticulate portion is 2.1. Gonoplac (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5F67A2DD670F8FD445BA7377BDE5B6C2" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Betacixius maculosus Tsaur &amp; Hsu, 1991, female A genitalia, lateral view B genitalia, ventral view C anal segment, dorsal view D tergite IX, caudal view E gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, ventral view F gonapophysis IX, lateral view G gonoplac, inner lateral view H posterior vagina, ventral view I posterior vagina, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.956.50195.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439750" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">5G</figureCitation>
) rod-like, 3.4 times longer than wide in lateral view. Posterior vagina pattern as shown in Figure 
<figureCitation id="78E8E68D73177C2EA5CBFFF21456ECC4" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Betacixius maculosus Tsaur &amp; Hsu, 1991, female A genitalia, lateral view B genitalia, ventral view C anal segment, dorsal view D tergite IX, caudal view E gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, ventral view F gonapophysis IX, lateral view G gonoplac, inner lateral view H posterior vagina, ventral view I posterior vagina, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.956.50195.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439750" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">5H, I</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
